product_name: FENTY BEAUTY by RihannaInvisimatte Instant Setting + Blotting Powder
summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeThis Fenty Beauty by Rihanna powder is universally sheer and sets, blurs + mattifies on the go. Invisimatte Instant Setting + Blotting Powder is a refillable, universal finishing powder that blurs the look of pores, absorbs shine and extends makeup wear all day.

how_to_use: Get ahead of shine and help your makeup last longer - the flexible formula can be used to set your look and blot throughout the day. Swipe the included sponge across the compact to pick up powder. Gently press and roll onto skin.

reviews.headline: Very brightening
reviews.comments: I really like this powder--it really brightened my skin and kind of made me look less like a sickly victorian child. I bought it in rose quartz. Worth it

reviews.headline: Love it
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Love this product. The packaging is cute and minimalistic. The product does not really have a smell in my opinion or maybe just like powder. It has great powdery kind of a nonexistent feel. It has good coverage and absolutely mattes down the skin.

reviews.headline: Setting Powder
reviews.comments: This lightweight setting/blotting powder kept me shine free all day without the need to reapply during the summer. I have normal skin and had no issues with the product. I do prefer to use a brush to apply rather than the applicator that it comes with. Overall I found this to be a good setting powder option.

reviews.headline: Oily skin girls… our time to shine!
reviews.comments: For us oily skin girls, we know how hard it is to keep our makeup intact all day. This blotting and blurring powder is truly incredible at doing its job. It's extended my makeup wear time for up to 12 hours total wear time on a hot, summer day. Though the packaging is a bit bulky for those who prefer a small handbag, I'll always make room for this powder on a steamy night out.

reviews.headline: A need if you get oily throughout the day!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This setting powder is perfect to throw in your purse and apply when you're a bit oily. I apply it under my eyes and my t-zone area. It instantly absorbs any oil and leaves my skin with an air-brushed finish.

reviews.headline: Winner!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I absolutely adore the finish and packaging of this product! The coverage is spot-on and lasts all day long. With my oily skin, it's a game changer—leaving my complexion fresh and free of any greasy feel or texture. I'm so impressed!

reviews.headline: Good
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Wonderful setting powder. Doesn't give the white cast via photos. Doesn't absorb oil as well as other ones I have used but would still purchase again.

reviews.headline: Perfect finish
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Love this! It has great coverage and a perfect finish! I would definitely recommend this to all my friends! It's especially great on mature skin! I have never used a product like this and have to say I am impressed!

reviews.headline: Great for oily skin girlies!!!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I have very oily skin, and the Fenty Beauty Invisimatte definitely does its job when it comes to keeping shine under control. It lasts really well throughout the day and adjusts nicely to my skin, which is a huge plus. The only downside is that it can sometimes look a little powdery or cakey on me, especially if I apply too much. Still, it's one of the better mattifying products I've tried, and I'd recommend it if you need long-lasting shine control. Additionally, the packaging is super compact and sleek. Overall, I love this product and I would recommend.

reviews.headline: Works well!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I love the packaging- it makes it super easy to use on the go. Here in the Arizona heat, setting powder is a must and this one is great at keeping my face looking good!

reviews.headline: Love the mirror and case!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] The packaging is so cute! I love that it comes with an applicator and has a mirror inside of it. It applies really well and makes your skin look great!

reviews.headline: Great Matte Finish Powder
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Good coverage. Nice matte finish when applied to oily areas; although I've noticed it can be a little cakey depending on where it's applied to on my face. For example, if I have a really dry patch or the foundation/BB/CC cream doesn't blended will with the powder, then there's a chance it could be cakey. Overall a good powder to use.

reviews.headline: Nice power
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This powder worked best for me over serum, under setting spray, before foundation. I have combination skin and when I tried it alone after my makeup it didn't last very long. After I changed where it was in my line up, it worked great.

reviews.headline: Perfect product
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This setting powder is amazing. As someone with oily skin makeup sometimes makes it worse. This takes all that away. The packaging is so cute and the powder pad is a perfect use and shape. I also love the leather on it.

reviews.headline: Great for blurring and setting your makeup
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This powder is a lifesaver! It instantly takes away shine without leaving any color or cakey finish. I love that it's truly universal and works perfectly for quick touch-ups throughout the day. Super lightweight and keeps my makeup looking fresh. I am a huge fan of Fenty products.

reviews.headline: Long lasting powder
reviews.comments: Gorgeous instant setting and blotting powder. This powder is long lasting and has a very pretty finish to it. The packaging is small enough to fit in a makeup bag too.

reviews.headline: Filtered Flawless Finish for Oily & Combo Skin Types
reviews.comments: The Fenty Beauty Invisimatte Instant Setting + Blotting Powder is perfect for oily & combination skin types. It aims to deliver instant mattification & a blurred, filtered finish, both for setting makeup & is great for touching up throughout the day

reviews.headline: Didn't love
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I will say me and setting powders aren't always friends haha I was excited to try this one. I have combo skin and the powder did make my dry areas look extra dry. Even with increasing my moisturizer, I still found my face would look a little kinky and they're setting powder didn't wear for multiple hours pretty well. I used the applicator it came with and also a brush, but didn't find either to be better than the other. I did like how soft and light it was!

reviews.headline: Best matte setting powder
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This is an amazing blurring powder and I think it the best I've tried so far. It leaves me with an amazing matte finish that's not too dry looking. It don't really have a scent to it. Overall I really like this!

media.headline: blot away oil shine, and let you shine

faceoff_positive.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I've been using the Fenty Beauty Invisimatte Instant Setting + Blotting Powder for a few weeks now, and I must say, it's become a staple in my makeup routine. The powder is exceptionally good at controlling oil throughout the day, which is a huge plus for my combination skin. It does a fantastic job of absorbing excess shine without making my face look cakey or heavy. Once applied, my face maintains a beautiful matte finish that lasts for hours on end. I love how lightweight the powder feels on the skin, it never feels suffocating or uncomfortable. The finely milled texture ensures a seamless blend, leaving no visible patches or unevenness. The translucent shade works well with my skin tone, providing a natural finish without adding any weird color tint. I've noticed that it helps set my foundation perfectly, reducing the need for frequent touch-ups. One of the best things about this powder is its versatility — I use it both as a setting powder and a blotting powder during the day. It's great for quick touch-ups, especially when I need to mattify my face on the go. The packaging is sleek and travel-friendly, making it easy to carry in my purse. However, I do have a small suggestion: I wish the puff had some kind of band or grip behind it for easier application. Sometimes, I find it a little tricky to hold onto the puff with such a small surface area. A band or textured grip would make application even more convenient. Aside from that minor detail, I'm very satisfied with the overall performance of the powder. The compact size means it doesn't take up much space in my makeup bag. It also doesn't leave any white cast or residue on my skin, which is a huge plus. The scent is very subtle and pleasant, not overpowering at all. I also appreciate how the powder doesn't settle into fine lines or cling to dry patches. It's suitable for all skin types, especially oily and combo skins like mine. The product truly lives up to its claim of providing an instant matte effect. I've received several compliments on how fresh and matte my face looks after using this powder. It works well with different primers and foundations, enhancing the overall finish. The longevity of the matte effect is impressive, even on hot, humid days. I would definitely recommend it to anyone struggling with excess oil. Overall, it's a reliable, high-quality setting and blotting powder. The only improvement I can suggest is enhancing the puff for more grip. If you're looking for a product that keeps your face matte and shine-free, this one is definitely worth trying. I will continue to repurchase it because it truly delivers excellent results. Fenty Beauty has nailed it with this formula, and I'm very happy with my purchase.
faceoff_positive.headline: No More Oily Face

faceoff_negative.comments: i have used the invisimatte powder for years, it's been my holy grail since it came out. I was really excited to see that Fenty came out with a new talc free formula and i understand that now they offer a new refill option for the powder inside which is amazing because it's less wasteful but i believe it's something to do with the new formula and or packaging that causes the pan to flip, crumble and break, making the product very useless and a waste of money considering it isn't cheap. This is the second one I've returned, at first i thought i had bought a defect one but it's happened again in the span of 2 months, very sad because this is my favorite powder. The new formula also doesn't do a good of a job at blurring the pores as the old one, maybe something to do with the talc. All in all i will perhaps give it a try again in the near future but will have to take it into my own hands to super glue the bottom of the pan onto to the compact…i haven't seen anyone else talk about it but i hope it's just a factory error and is fixed soon.
faceoff_negative.headline: not as good as the old one
